cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep learning approach to learn hierarchical features for tracking, which involves training a convolutional neural network. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with video sequences, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on tracking suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO), as tracking is an important task in robotics applications.
